body: These are okay... They fit fine and they're comfortable to wear.... The reason I give it 3 stars is because when I got them one of the sides played at a significantly lower volume also don't underestimate the short distance comments. I didn't think it would be that big of a deal , but it's actually extremely annoying because it doesn't just stop playing music when you was too far it completely disconnects. Meaning if you are listing to music in the kitchen and you pause it to go to the other side of your house but you leave the set on it will completely disconnect. This bothers me because I previously had a pair of MPow Jaws where this didn't happen at all. Of course those are slightly more expensive but they they had zero problems other than being big and ugly. Also the clip that came with it kept falling off and it only stopped falling then I lost it. Which is annoying because if you're going to run or something you need that clip. So 5/10 probably would recommend to some one I don't like...the battery life on these is also exceptionally short.... Oh and when I bought these I remember the overall rating being at 4/5 seeing how it is somehow different makes me feel scammed.

Bought these headphones back in December of 2017. I had them for a week before I used them. I used them for about a week a few hours a day until the charge died. Then charged them overnight and used them for 1 minute and they ran out of power. So I put them to charge for 4 hours and tried using them again. The battery die a 1 after turned them on. So I returned them to the seller. They received them on December 23. I received an email on the 23 that I would receive my refund in 2 to 3 business days. Here it is about a month later and still no refund. I even sent them an email and they never replied.
great product. the sound quality is really good. I like that the buttons are a little bigger, easier to use. light weight. sync with iwatch  with no problems.

Love the fit of the earbuds. They actually stay in my ears. Had a problem with the sound on the first pair. Contacted seller and they sent me a new pair, no questions asked! Happy with the sound now. Good Bluetooth buds for the price!

The earbuds are alright. But the usb cable that came with it to charge the earbuds literally couldn’t handle the voltage from my computers USB port and started to burn and smell. It almost burned my fingers trying to unplug it, it was so hot to the touch. Product support is also not available.

I bought these as a Christmas gift for my husband but when they arrived I wanted to make sure the sound quality was something he was going to appreciate. The Bluetooth was super easy to connect to my phone and the sound quality was surprisingly really good. My fingers are crossed that he likes them.
Horrible charging, the battery only last maybe 3 hours. And i had issues with the other person I’m talking to not hearing me clearly. I wouldn’t it again.
works goood
Definitely much louder from the right headphone than the left. Poor quality. I would not purchase again.
When these earphones were delivered they didn't work at all, not even when I charged them for 9 hours
Poor sound quality, unbalanced volumes in each ear, and they lasted less than a week and then would not turn on.
Only use them for a few days and side stop working
Really good earbuds for the price.
The sound quality is really good.
low coverage range.

This was a gift for a girl. Easy to connect just hold down power button until it tells you your searching. Girlfriend didn't really like them because the red square part is a little to big and when she has them in she was said they hurt her ear. So I took them back. they fit fine for me little oversized, but the sound is great with nice highs and good sounding deep bass. holds charge for about 4 hours. for the price im happy with them and that they are wireless. would probably spend the little bit more for better shaped ones if I could go back

Just got mine and so far, so good. If anything goes wrong, I will revise my review. USE THE SOUND EQUALIZER ON YOUR PHONE! At first, I thought the sound was too bassy and muffled....was disappointed. Another reviewer mentioned equalizing the sound, which I didn't realize I could do. Made all the difference!

Had the headphones for 24 hours and all of a sudden the sound would diminish.  Then it would start to power off on its own.  The buttons stopped working.  Bought 3 for holiday presents.  Now thats embarassing.  Absolute garbage.
Poor quality construction and very bad sound quality
This thing is easy to use, fits good, and the sound is amazing.  I'm impressed.
Pros: Decent sound, works great with Bluetooth, comfortable.Cons: terrible battery life

They synced easily. I started wearing them and the right bud, with the battery attached, kept pulling out of my ear. I switched the ear bud covers to a larger one hoping it would fit tighter but it did the same thing. Then the sound started to crackle. It was intermittent at first but before the first charge had ran out, about 4 hours, they died completely. Sent them back.
Worked for an hour and then wouldn't work anymore. If that's the battery life then this product is garbage. Not happy with it at all.
The headphones have good sound. The contol box is a bit bulky.

Plugged this in and my brand new iPhone 7 Plus said "this accessory is not supported" and it didn't work at all - neither the charger nor the audio component. I threw it in the trash which is where it belongs.
Didn’t work consistently on iPhone 8 with iOS 11. Audio dropped out, didn’t seem to fit the port very well.
Plugged it in and it worked for a minut or two then my phone popped up “software not supported” and couldn’t get it to work again

-5 stars! Didn’t work AT ALL. A big notification popped up immediately upon plugging it in saying it’s not compatible! And it didn’t work AT ALL! Totally bummed! The whole no headphone jack on the new iPhone SUCKS!
Doesn’t work at all. Not to charge my iphone7 or to play music via aux cord adapter. Very disappointed in this product.
Don't work I keep getting a message saying it does not support my device I have iPhone 7 plus  waste of money

Started looking at the 5 star reviews because it is hard to believe when there are so many 1 star. What i noticed is that 95% of the 5 stars have only reviewed this one item. Many of them have an item on their wish list and, hard to believe, but most want this double pack of a cheap Chinese flashlight. Not one of these 5 stars are verified purchases , so they didn't purchase this item on Amazon.  What these scammers hope is that you purchase and decide it is not worth your trouble to ship it back. Either way, they figure Amazon pays for shipping so it doesn't matter.

I absolutely love this charger for my iPhone 7Plus. First, I was skeptical about even buying the iPhone 7 because of the lack of a headphone jack. However, this adapter solves all those issues. I can easily listen to music while charging my phone which I wasn't able to do before buying this adapter. It works great! I also love that there are two ports so I can plug into both places at once. With this adapter, it works like any of the other previous versions of the iPhone so I would highly recommend!

I listen to music at work as well as on my commute so it's important to have enough battery to do this. The audio + charge means that I can charge it at work at the same time as listening to my music. It's quite light and small so easy to carry in my purse and I don't notice any difference in the audio. Recommended!!

I have tried a few of these adapters and so far this is my favorite. It is about as small as it could be and constructed very well. Working 10 hr days and listening to the music with my headphones drains my battery so quickly. This adaptor not only lets me keep my phone charge but I can also enjoy my favorite music. I'm pleased and I think anyone who purchased this will be happy with it!

Great product, perfect for charging and connecting your earphones together. It's also great if you don't like the wireless earphones , you can just insert your adapter and it's ready to use with your traditional earphones. With this adapter you can keep enjoying your music while charging your phone.The material looks and feels sturdy and has been working perfectly for me. I would recommend to anyone that needs one
Item does not work. Using an iPhone 7+ with iOS 11.01, device does not recognise this accessory.Very disappointed with this product.

I love this so much! I bought another one on here and it didn't work at all so I had to return it! I got this one super fast and it works perfect I love that I can charge my phone and charge it at the same time! I always watch Netflix at night but that's right when my phone dies so it's either keep everyone up or charge my phone so now I don't have to decide!!

There's better out there does exactly what it is supposed to do,nothing more,nothing less Very inexpensive in comparison to other options on the market I absolutely love this product Brilliant device! Super fast shipping.
Works well on both ends, I have no complaints. It's just really a new thing for me, I've been used to plugging headphones right into the phone's jack right away out of habit.

These work great. Appear to be the exact same quality as the one that was part of my IPhone 7. I find no difference in the sound quality.Item worked as expected. However, I had to take my protective case off to plug the item into my phone.
It is a scam it doesn’t work on the iPhone 7..... Don’t buy it what so ever
This is my 2nd try to buy this kind of product on Amazon, and it does not work again!!! It says it is not supported by Iphone. Had to go to Apple to buy their product.

Its a small device so it fits in my pocket with my phone. Easily portable for use anytime too.The phone charges just as fast as the original cord. We were also able to use this with headphones as well as the original apple headphones that came with the phone.

"Quick delivery !!! Thank you for selling an iPhone 7plus charger that works with the iOS 10.3 update. I've used it all day at work - listening to music while charging my phone ... #life at work just got better! "

Good adapter.Haven't had any trouble with it like others seem to have. Its an everyday use for me to have in my car to charge and hear music and it works great. Simple awesome solution with the iPhone 7.
It's perfect for my IPhone 7. I use my phone throughout the day so I need to eventually charge and still listen to my stuff.
Connector and my phone shell seamless, very perfect.Charging my iphone 7s really fast, they are still very good! Strongly recommend this product.
Ordered it for a friend as a gift,Works as expected and no complaints for the price,works great.
Pretty good! It works as expected (charging + music).

I'm delighted I ordered this 2 in 1 Adapter I can listen to my favourite music or watch videos or movies in my phone while charging which I can't normally do before as I need to wait for my phone to charge 1st before I can even use my headset again.The size of the adapter is small enough to put in my bag or take it with me everywhere I go.Cool stuff.
With this iPhone lightning port splitter I can now charge my phone AND listen to my headphones. No idea why apple decided to get rid of the phone jack headphone port,I highly recommend it!

Very nice product! Exectly what I'm looking for. the quality is super good and better quality than most of those cheap stuff on Amazon. I had to return similar stuff twice but I don't need to return this one now because it's exactly what I wanted.

I can put my music in my ears and zone out and get all creative with my job. Ever since they removed the 3.5 mm port from the iphone 7, it has been a pain since you can't charge your phone and listen to music at the same time. This product fixes that.

The audio quality is better and now the audio syncs exactly with the video. Massive improvement and the quality of the device seems good. It seems like it will last a long time!!This works very well and I have had no problems.

I ordered this iPhone 7 splitter for my sister. This thing is very handy for multiple uses at once. She is very pleased with it. It works great and seems to be a good quality splitter. Can't go wrong with it. Great price for a great product.

It's a prefect adapter that solve my big problem that I cannot charge and listen to music at the same time. I hate this terrible design for iPhone 7 which make me furious. It's helpful and worth the price.

This fixed problem that my iPhone 7 Plus couldn't charge while listening to music with my earbuds at the same time. I brought this adapter. It's very convenient to use and has saved my time to charge!
I prefer wired headphone instead of wireless headphone. This little one solves the problem between charging and listening. Great product, I would recommend this product.
Connects wonderfully with my iphone7 and does the job, exactly what i needed. Perfect sound quality and fits just right with the phone and headphone jack.
At last my wife can listen to music and charge her iPhone 7+ at the same time, now she is happy(so am I). The audio quality has no degradation.
Nice quality and works well. Its a small device so it fits in my pocket with my phone 7. Easily portable for use anytime too. Would recommend to anyone interested.
Excellent adapter for connecting my iphone 7+. Let me able to plug into my new devices without any issue and reuse old cords. Works great.
Out of the box, works fine (on day 1) - will follow up after more rigorous use and after the next iOS update or two..
Great concept on allowing it to function in both ways - charging and listening! The product is compact and functional.
It works just like the authentic adapter for my iphone 7. The quality is good and the price is decent.
I'm seriously happy with this purchase. Awesome adapter with great sound quality.
Sons birhday present he loves them, complained about short battery life but I found out he listened for 8 hours straight.
My son loves these and what more could I ask for. they hold a charge nicely, look stylish.

Perhaps I received the wrong product but no noise cancelling ability on the unit I received just regular Bluetooth headset. Sent both back for refund. I wish they would have worked to cancel sounds as advertised but they did not.
So amazing! Awesome for the price.
Product works great and very comfortable. I notice if the volume is super high though the music is audible to others. But overall for walking around a campus they work great!
Excellent sound, easy to use, lightweight. Love it.
I could hear other noise (almost like another "channel") and others could hear my music.

I have been using bose sountrue headphones for the past year and wanted to give these a try because they are bluetooth and are noise canceling. I have never been impressed witn any headphones noise canceling abilities, these are as good as any in that respect. These headphones have very good sound and a great battery life, however. They also seem to be constructed well and durable.

Wanted a cheap headset to watch tv at night without disturbing the other half. Found these and looked okay. Impressed with the quality. These do not appear typical of cheapo Chinese goods. The assembly and finish is actually quite nice. They are comfortable to wear, at least for an hour or two. They seal up pretty well against my ears and the ear pads are very soft. If I continued use beyond two hours, I suspect my ears my become sore as other reviews have said. The sound quality is pretty good. They have some bass to them, more than enough for television. Didn't have much issue connecting to the Bluetooth transmitted which I also just bought. Took a couple minutes to get it worked out, and I had to go through the connection process again a few days later, but no biggie. The only thing I can complain about, and it's not really a fair complaint, is the squeaky smooth frame rubs against my pillow and echoes the sound through the headphones. So, I have to keep my head perfectly still if I don't want to hear the rubbing. Sorta sounds like when you rub your hand against a balloon...echoing in your ears. I recommend these to anyone who is drawn by the price and style. You'll be getting exactly what you think you are.

Great quality and fast shipping. Seller has great communication with customers.I actually bought these for my son to use for this coming school year. But purchased early for him to use on our summer vacation. (10:30 hrs. On the road, in mid-size suv.) And the worked wonderfully!I couldn't hear games and movies while trying to navigate. And her was oblivious to anything else in the world. Noise cancellation! Great.

I was looking for some over ear headphones that I could use to work out with. I chose these because of the reviews and pricing. I chose over ear primarily because I wanted wireless, and headphones that weren't going to constantly fall out my ears. These head phones come in a plane packaging, with an aux cable and soft carrying bag for the headphones. The headphones fit pretty snug which is nice because when i went running they were falling off or sliding back, they held up perfecting fine. The sound quality was really good, I expected some pretty bad lows or even bad highs but the headphones have a great balance. Pairing it by bluetooth to my cell phone was pretty easy (if you can follow directions). The build quality is ok, the gloss black seems like it would scratch easily. I use this for both running and lifting weights, and it hasnt had any issues with falling off at all. Great headphones for the price

Wow. The bass is incredible, the sound response. Here is what I did, I decided, since all of these cheap headsets get ok ratings I only purchased four star ones. I got five different kinds, this one stands out, no questions, hands down, major winner. I plan to buy three pairs and just forget about it. If I break them, misplace them, give them away, whatever, I'm covered. You can't go wrong. I use them for running and the long cord is great, no issues. Sure they get a little sweaty but I can hear the oncoming slaughter (unlike in ear headphones), the bass is great, my ears are not sore. Fantastic.

I've only had these for an afternoon but I already love them. I have a large head and certain headphones pressing into my ears or scalp cause migraines. So far, these have felt very comfortable and the sound quality is excellent. I was able to easily pair them with my Nexus 5. I'm still figuring out how to pair them with my Asus Chromebook. They are circumaural (cover the ear completely) and build quality seems good for the price. I bought these to replace a pair of wireless sennheiser RD160s that stopped working. I will update this review if these give me trouble after I get more use out of them but I am already impressed with them, given the price.

I wanted an inexpensive pair of bluetooth headphones to use at the gym, and this item is perfect. The directions were easy to follow and set-up was a breeze. I love the bag to keep them in and the cord to use when the battery runs low or when I want them wired. Great purchase.

Arrived fast, work great, bluetooth works while charging. A quality purchase - well worth the $$$. But if I'm being absolutely honest, the only thing I would've have improved on is the design - slightly, The headphones look very elegant (I like the brush metal look) that you see on the 1 side of the headphone, but would've preferred if both sides looked like that (uniformity), & made the icons in Blk, & made each icon w/ a groove (like braille) so I can feel where the buttons are on the side while I'm wearing them. But aside from my nit-pickyness, again a absolutely great purchase!
There is no noise cancelling at all. It's just a regular bluetooth headphone. It's false advertisement.

These headphones are spectacular. While they are a little weak on the low end, they produce a sound that defies their price. They are crisp, and clear on most tracks, and if you are looking for a comfortable set of cans to wear, these will fit the bill. They are even comfortable with glasses on. I have not yet tested using the chord for the operation of these, however, I will have the opportunity to shortly as I am traveling internationally with them soon. If anything I experience changes my opinion, I will update as necessary.
I love these headphones. I didn't want to spend 200 dollars on beats so I figured these would be the next best thing and boy was I right! I love them. I also use them for running and they work fine.

Audio and build quality are pretty good. My only complaint is the "mic" on this - cannot get people to hear me. I would recommend these as a decent pair of inexpensive bluetooth headphones, wouldn't recommend them as a headset. UPDATE - After my initial concerns with the headset, the company had reached out to explain my concerns and wanted to resolve the issue. We did some troubleshooting and they had ultimately sent me a replacement that I am able to use the mic now. Thank you.

These headphones are quite nice. They fit well and operate as stated. I purchased them to operate with my 55 series Samsung TV. The 55 series will not sync directly to the headphones (the 64 series will) so I purchased a Bluetooth adaptor which synced with the headphones easily. These headphones support two Bluetooth devices allowing me to sync my iPhone as a secondary device. I couldn't be happier with the outcome and yes, I would recommend to friends and family.
These are soooooo good. Great sound quality and sound reducing. Worth the money.

I bought these for use with my computer which has Bluetooth built in, however I've also used this for my phone with great results. The mic can be very quiet and only "telephone" quality, but the audio coming from the headphones is great. I suggest if you have bigger ears like me you take them off every so often and let your ears have a rest. Long battery life is a huge plus. These also come with a bag so you can easily port them around since they do fold up.

These are 5-star headphones _in context_. Compared to a pair of audiophile super-engineered headphones, of course not. But for a pair of headphones you can toss in your backpack and take with you for under 15 bucks? Really, really good headphones. Clean sound, surprisingly strong bass. A bargain!
everything is working fine, you can hear even the smallest of sounds. The fit is good and you can adjust them to fit your head,
Deceptive. These are NOT noise cancelling. Very uncomfortable, they hurt  your ears after 20 minutes. Terrible. Returned.

Bought these headphones on a whim after having to return another pair that came defective and I'm so glad I did. They feel very sturdy and pair with my phone immediately. The sound is pretty good and they get very loud. The only con would be that they make your ears very warm when working out, but that wouldn't be a surprise to anyone considering the design of these headphones.

Needed a 2nd set of headphones. Decided to purchase a different brand this time. These are much better than the brand I purchased a few momths ago at a similar price. Easy to operate. Holds a charge all day. Plug in or use bluetooth. Great sound. They fold for easy transport. A little heavier, but more padding in the ear area and sturdier.

These headphones are amazing! I've been looking for a nice pair, one that I wouldn't have to spend a fortune on. I've heard not so spectacular things about Beats headphones (which is what I was originally looking at). But these are perfect! The cushions are perfect and don't put pressure on my ears like another pair I had. Definitely would recommend these. Music and videos sound great through their speakers.

Absolutely love these headphones. They fit perfectly. They do not press on my ears and cause them to become sore like others I have used. They are an excellent quality too. They fold up nicely. They are just perfect and I would Highly recommend to anybody. So glad I purchased these bluetooth headphones.
I love these headphones. I didn't want to spend 200 dollars on beats so I figured these would be the next best thing and boy was I right! I love them. I also use them for running and they work fine.

The only reason I'm giving this product and the seller 5 stars is because there is no option to give them 6 stars. Very comfortable to wear, the performance is outstanding and the shipping was super fast, what else can you ask for?

Very comfortable, even when worn over my eyeglasses. The sound is great, and they work within at least a 10 foot range of my cell phone (haven't tested exact limit of wireless range.) They don't require charging every day. These have been one of my favorite purchases in a long time! They've truly revolutionized listening to music for me, since I don't have to worry about tangled cords or earbuds falling out.

I just got this headphone. It impressed me by its lightweight, good quality and the price. The most important thing is that it works great and more than I expected. It fits my little mp3 player.I am going to buy one more for my kid. I highly recommend it.

Finally wire free with this headset. Arrived on time and packaged well. Came with a travel bag and connecting cords. Connects to me desktop computer every time. Fits well and is not tight. Ears don't feel sore after hours of movie binges. Sounds great when watching movies and music videos. I plug it in every night after movies when done for the night. So far no problems.

Needed a 2nd set of headphones. Decided to purchase a different brand this time. These are much better than the brand I purchased a few momths ago at a similar price. Easy to operate. Holds a charge all day. Plug in or use bluetooth. Great sound. They fold for easy transport. A little heavier, but more padding in the ear area and sturdier.
First off, these are not $100 headphones; but the quality of sound is way better than I expected. So much so, that I bought a 2nd pair as backup. For under $10 I do not think you can do better.

These are amazing headphones for the price. Contrary to some reviews I have read about being uncomfortable after wearing for an hour, I have not experienced any type of "fatigue" with long term use. The sound is great and they perform as advertised!

Sounds great. However, for an older individual, I hoped for a slightly easier pairing process. Otherwise, I'm very pleased with this product. Your follow-up email did the trick. I am now easily paired. 4 stars raised to 5 stars!

Been using them for a week, only minor issue I have is how one button does several things. Unless I'm doing it wrong the on/off/pair button are all the same. So when you turn off the headset it starts to pair then shuts off a sec later. Not a big issue, would of preferred another button for the pairing.

The product came one day earlier than expected inside a very secure cardboard box. It sounds great and has really good base and sound quality. So far i haven't noticed any problems with Bluetooth connectivity or any issues for that matter. Definitely worth the price.

I'm actually quite pleased with this set. I had tried it with an older bluetooth USB stick, and the sound was horrible. But with a newer bluetooth transmitter, the sound was lovely. With the transmitter hooked up to my stereo/tv, I can now watch and listen to TV when I can't sleep at 3:00 AM without waking up the spouse.

Very nice bluetooth headphones. They feel great around the ears and are very comfortable, and do a good job blocking out sound with their design. The sound is quite good for the price as well which is great. Intuitive connection and syncing process as well, for my laptop at any rate! I would recommend.

Fast shipping. And the headphones have the look, feel and sound of expensive headphones, but without the expensive price. They are very good headphones that I use while working out and just working. Also they filter out a lot of external noise. All around, the best product I found for the price paid.

Holy heck, these are great headphones! I honestly can't say I was expecting much due to the price, but these are fantastic! I wanted wireless headphones, but definitely didn't want to spend hundreds on the Beats. These have great sound, were easy to pair, and are compact for travel. With iPhone no longer having headphone jacks, these are perfect. They also come with a headphone jack cord if you want to use it, but the battery life is so great it's not even really necessary. However, it is nice that they included it. Don't hesitate with these, they are awesome!

These headphones are a steal! Very comfortable and stylish too. I had people asking about them before I entered work...they look great and sound great. Connection was a snap. Operation is super easy. I have had other brands in the past that were good...these are FAR better and a steal of a price.

The best wireless headphone I have ever used and for the price I could not be happier. I am very impressed with the battier life to good to be true but it is true 15hr of usage and I still have 50% battier life reaming. Keep up the good work.

I've only had it for about two hours; it was charged and easy to pair to my phone. It does seem like the volume sometimes changes by a simple move of your head. I wish the volume could go a little higher, but realize most things like this have to be "designed for our protection".
Wow! For the price great quality. Easy to connect, great volume, and the noise cancellation is acceptable. Would definitely recommend.

Great headphones for a great price! Bluetooth was a little quite when I answered my phone but that very well could have been because I didn't have the volume up high enough. Super happy with this purchase!!

The product came one day earlier than expected inside a very secure cardboard box. It sounds great and has really good base and sound quality. So far i haven't noticed any problems with Bluetooth connectivity or any issues for that matter. Definitely worth the price.

Sounds great. However, for an older individual, I hoped for a slightly easier pairing process. Otherwise, I'm very pleased with this product. Your follow-up email did the trick. I am now easily paired. 4 stars raised to 5 stars!
sounds great, the battery lasts wayyy longer than expected. this is my fourth time using it, yesterday used it for about 7 hours and the batter is still at the 80-90% mark

Awesome sound out of these cheap headphones. Very comfortable to wear all day while I'm at work. I have some background noise but when I wear these I don't hear anything except the music. I would definitely recommend these.

So far so good.. my husband loves them. So far he has lived in them since he got them. They are super loud, I can hear them when they are hung around my husband's neck. The charge send to last a few hours and the headphones were easy to connect to his iPhone 6S plus.
Surprisingly good sound. Way better than I expected from $6 headphones.

I really can't say enough about the quality of sound, ease of pairing and feel of the headphones for the price I paid. I've already recommended your headphones to friends who enjoy listening to good music with a great set of ears.
First thing is the price was great. Second it's AWESOME! So comfortable to use and easy to connect. Makes listening to music totally worth it now when doing any outdoor activities.
I use them for workouts because previously I was never able to find any that'd stay on my head. The wireless aspect is amazing and it also comes with a headphone jack cord. No complaints whatsoever
At this early usage, the head phones are working as advertised. They are more comfortable then the pair that these replaced. I wear the headset for hours at a time and every day.

I have a 300$ pair of Sony wireless headphones for my TV and I wanted to buy a cheaper pair for my PC but these headphones are ten times better than the Sony. I am thinking of buying another pair to replace the Sony.

Solid sound, pairs easily, affordable. I use these to work out. So much better than ear buds. They are not designed for exercise, so they get a bit sweaty, but I liked them enough to buy another pair for my partner.

I really wanted these to cancel out airplane noise but they absolutely did not. In fact, the first time I tried to listen to a song while on a flight, I couldn't hear anything at all. I thought there was something wrong with my phone or the song. Finally I connected my ancient $9 earbuds and bang, there was Jimi Hendrix singing loud and clear above the airplane noise. I was quite disappointed. And women, listen up: they were comfortable but too big for my head (as well as my adult daughter's) -- and we don't have particularly small heads, just female heads. I don't know why manufacturers don't understand that women have smaller ears/heads than men. I mean, we're half the population, right?! The sound was actually really good when I tested them in my house, but I don't walk around my house wearing headphones. Forget gym use -- they'd be sliding off my head in no time. Needless to say, I returned them.

The on-ear (not over-the-ear) design is uncomfortable for me.  The headphones are loud and very bass-heavy.  The mic makes me sound like I've fallen in a well - unusable for business calls (IMO).The tiny buttons, worthless manual (with tiniest print I've ever seen), and slightly broken English in pairing prompts could be forgiven if it was a strong performer, but it is not.In my office, the bluetooth range is about 3m, not 10m.  The on-ear design is noisier (even with noise cancellation) than over-the-ear competitors that have no noise-cancellation.I also bought some M-POW 059's for my 9 year-old.  The 059's were a few dollars cheaper and yet better in every category:  sound of headphones, sound of mic, comfort, user interface, and closer to 20m of bluetooth range.  The 059's also had a much more solid feel to them, folded for transport, and can be used in a cabled mode.

As someone mentioned, the instruction manual was illegible to any eye. Purchase a magnifying glass along with these headphones.To save you time, the button functions from bottom to top:- bottom button is on/off - you must hold for 4-5 seconds before it turns off or on (and the voice tells you it has). It doubles as the pairing button- 2nd button from bottom - makes a call to the last person you called if your phone is paired with the headphones- next button up - skips the song playing (at least on Pandora)- top button repeats the songI am a classical musician and have listened extensively to speakers and headphones of all kinds.The quality is actually quite dark and muffled and of course it can't be controlled. Hearing podcasts or I would think a person on the phone is very cloudy.On the positive side, the headphones are extremely comfortable!

These ratings have to be fake.  These earphones are just awful. Sound is good, but loses signal if line of sight is slightly broken. Don't tune your head slightly, take a bite of yogurt, or sneeze. Just awful.

Short version: awful unacceptable sound, bait. and switch branding, illegible instructions, cheap product.Longer version:First start with the packaging.  Inside the Amazon box the product packaging was coming loose with the product spilling out.  Maybe it was the shipper's issue.Second the instructions were very minimal. I mean literally minimal.  I could barely read the instructions.  The font size may have been 4 points and could not figure them after taking a picture and zooming on the pic.  Read .. cheap, cheap, cheap.To take the cake, the sound was awful.  Not just a bit bad, it was NOT ACCEPTABLE.Finally, the brand on the package is "Ette".  It was advertised as "Labvon".  There was a small sticker with faded print saying "Labvon".In summary .. cheap Chinese cheapo s***.  They offer to replace it if you give them 5 stars.  Probably explains why this is so highly rated.

So I got these lights today and I have to say, they are a LOT of fun. First off, getting them hooked up to my router was a breeze. I use an extender, and I just used the app (Android in my case) and it was very easy, no problems at all. Yes, you have to do each bulb once, but once you have it connected, it's very easy to rename the bulbs and group them into groups (in my case for example, 3 bulbs for one fixture). The app itself is incredibly easy to use. You have individual colors (just a color wheel), then you have regular warm white/yellow for normal use (with dim) on another screen, a 3rd screen allows you to do the built in programs (such as cross fades, individual fades, and strobe effects) with a slider for quickness, and 4th screen is the custom modes that you can program yourself and just use with a touch of a button. It is pretty easy to turn on the remote feature, which will let you control your lights from anywhere you have internet access. The only downside is each bulb has to be programmed for each device you want to use. But you only have to do it once. When the bulbs are keyed in to that device, short of your router going bad, you should be good to go for years. My kid and I have been spending an hour just playing around with the different modes. It does have a 5th screen/mode, which is music, but to be honest, I didn't find that particularly enjoyable. It supposedly strobes based on the music (and the music has to be on your device), but I didn't think it was all that great at synching with the music. Perhaps in future versions of the app, you can stream music from Youtube or Pandora or such, and maybe give more options for synch. But otherwise, yes, the bulbs are expensive, but they will last a long time, and really give you full control. I hope the company starts doing other types of bulbs, such as recessed lights, candle base lights, and more variety in wattage. Overall, very highly recommended.

I purchased this light to be used as a wake up light to help me drag myself out of my slumber. It handles that task as well as so many others extremely well. The bulb itself is built well and has a large metal heat sink as the base to help remove heat. The lumen output is comparable to a 60 watt bulb as stated and the colors produced are rich and brilliant. What honestly impressed me the most was with the level of customer service I experienced. While using the application I sent an email to the support team about a possible improvement within the app. I received a response the following morning asking for clarification and to bring in other members of their team. This email chain continued that morning and at the end I was left feeling satisfied with their responses. Buy this for an awesome Wi-Fi enabled smart bulb that is on par with Hue and be confident about your purchase because of their support.

These bulbs are a lot of fun! I bought 2 and have had them a day so far. I am a bit of a tech novice, but I had them both set up in about 10 minutes after resetting the app on my iPhone (deleted the app off phone and downloading the app again). Each bulb is a separate line item on the app once you set it up. To change name to "Living Room" (etc), click and hold on the name on the main list and it will give you a prompt to "Device Rename". You can have each bulb on 2 (or more) separate phones as well. You can control them with each phone. There are a few glitches in the app on occasion with finding the bulbs, but I keep hitting the sync button and the bulbs eventually show up. Other than that, the app is pretty easy to use. You can set up timers for use while traveling. You can control the bulbs away from your WiFi with the "Remote" tab on the app, but I have not used this to verify yet. Fun options are changing color, set to change colors to music on your phone, preset color fade/strobe options with speed control, make custom light color settings with speed controls, dimming capabilities, and "disco" mode changes color with sounds through the microphone on phone (so it will work with any music and sound from TV, stereo, voice, etc). So far the bulbs have been a great buy!!!!

I bought two of these and they are far superior than the InaRock bulbs. The color quality is great and I can leave them in to use as normal white bulbs when needed since they can do a warm white function. The app is easy to use and allows me to sync up multiple bulbs easily so that they all change colors at the same time. I can adjust the brightness of the bulbs from very bright to very dim. The mic setting makes the bulbs react to external noise in a very cool, club-like way. I recommend turning their sensitivity to low when you use this setting. My favorite feature is the custom setting, which allows me to input my own sequences. This allows more random color sequences at parties, which feels more natural.

I bought this in both the wifi and bluetooth version. I'm giving the bluetooth 4 stars only because I prefer the wifi version...which I am giving 5 stars. Super easy to set up both bulbs. My kids absolutely love them. They want them for their rooms too, and I will definitely be ordering again. The customer service is PHENOMENAL! Super fast replies, and just really nice people! The ONLY thing I would love to see added is the ability to control through Alexa (Echo). These are definitely the way to go. Some of the other brands are crazy expensive. These are affordable and super cool. My kids have their favorite colors programmed in. Love being able to set mood lights for movies. You can set them to turn on at certain times too.

The bulb and the ease of the app work very well. The colors are pretty. I was very disappointed in the brightness. Somewhere I had read that this bulb was equivalent to a 60 watt incandescent bulb. That is the only reason I purchased this particular brand. It isn't. It is barely equal to a 30 watt.

The headset has a strong enough magnet to hold the earpieces together and the sound is reasonably good. The reason why I returned it was that it didn't hold charge for more than a half a day on standby.

It's not quite as bright as expected, but for our living room, it works just fine.

I bought these a few weeks ago and have had a chance to use them in a variety of workouts. During my first few weeks, I haven't had any problems with these headphones. If that changes, I will update this review. 1. Quality- They have a solid feel. Easy to use buttons all on one side with a few helpful short cuts built in (ie answering phone calls, skipping, pausing, etc). They have a great sound for working out. They definitely have more than enough noise to hurt your ears, so heads up on making sure they didn't sneak to full volume. I'm not an audiophile, but these definitely have a solid, well balanced sound. If you're looking for a workout headphone with good noise, these will work. 2. Comfort- The earbuds are soft and fit well inside my ear. They send an array of sizes, so everyone should find a fit. The soft rubber that hooks over your ear is just enough keep them over your ears, even while running, but isn't a solid piece pressing into your skull. . 3.Charge- These have a pretty decent battery. I used mine over four 1.5-2 hr workouts. On the fourth one they started telling me low battery. You can get a quick charge on them and be ready to go. They come with a variety of charging accessories. It charges off a micro usb, but they send you a lighting cable charger too. Also, a car charger with two ports and a short usb cord. Lots of extras 4. COST- Best bang for my buck as far as Im concerned. I'm super happy with these for what I paid and what I got in return. Hope this helps you out with your shopping!

I was able to use these headphones while at the gym yesterday, and they were the best I’ve tried so far. I’ve previously tried Neo JDX, Avantree Jogger Pro Sweat, and a few others that I don't recall the brands. The ActivBuds were super easy to charge, pair, and wear. I have small ears, but was able to use the buds that were on the headphones, and did not need to use any of the alternative size gel-ear pods. My first impression – I used them while on the treadmill doing a 3-mile run at about a pace of 6, and they felt comfortable and did not fall out of my ear at any point. As I moved to the weight area, I found myself wanting to skip songs, and change the volume, and was able to do both with no problem. My favorite feature is that I was able to skip songs forward and backward. The best feature is the ability to pause the song when I needed to talk to my workout partner, and I was able to do that a simple click of the button. All of these features are available on the right ear piece. One other cool feature that I found most helpful for my small ears, is that the ear loop is made of a something that feels very malleable, and I was able to easily wrap around my ear, which is how I think they stayed in place while I was running. Overall, I’m very pleased with these, and especially for the price and have actually ordered another pair to gift to my boyfriend. He currently has the wireless headphones Beats By Dre (which are nearly 3 or 4 times the cost of these), and he is not very pleased with them and was definitely envious of all of the neat features and sound quality that these offered.

For the first few months these headphones worked flawlessly, truly waterproof, great sound quality, and comfort. I have used these headphones everyday since I purchased them. That has caused some technical issues. Every now and then they would start not working right, first they would not sound right. Since these headphones didn't work properly, I contacted their customer service and they would tell me to do a factory reset.(hold down multi function button for 7 secs while they were being charged) That worked for a while, but my recent issue (which happened months later). Just the headphones not sounding how they used too. They weren't as loud as they used to be and one side played next to no sound. This is an issue for me so when I contacted their customer service, they are apparently sending me a new pair to replace the old one. (Since their go to problem solver factory reset didn't work) For those of you who are on the fence to buy these, buy them. They have a 1 year factory warranty and great customer service. I highly recommend them.

These are lightweight, comfortable, pair seamlessly, have great battery life, and offer very decent audio quality. I really have no complaints after one week of heavy use. They've been perfect for me at the gym and during my commute. The water resistance is great (I've showered with them, no problem) and they stay put when I'm working out. I was concerned they looked bulky in the photos, but they're really very light and comfortable when in my ears. As far as audio goes, to my ears, all earphones tend to fall into 2 categories of audio quality: on the tinny side or the bassy side. These have a slightly bassy quality, but it's not obnoxious. I find it pretty pleasant for my wide ranging tastes (mostly podcasts, jazz, rock, classical, and occasional hip-hop during workouts). They arrived packaged very nicely and, as noted by other reviewers, come with a host of accessories that really make the value unbeatable: a car charger, 2 usb cable (long and short), a zip case, multiple cup sizes, and a lightning cable. I am very happy with the purchase. Will post an update if anything fails, but I don't anticipate it.

I've bought a few types of wireless headphones in the $17-$30 range and they worked fine, but died after about 3 months. I use mine specifically for gym workout and what I like about these is not just the sound (great sound and great bass) but that they do NOT have the mic and volume on the actual cable (it's on the ear piece). I found it's annoying when you have that extra piece of plastic throwing the weight of the cable off balance while you're running, walking, etc.. They're super comfortable and stay in your ear really well which is sometimes a problem for me. Comes with two different lengths of cables to charge along with listed accessories. Great headphones... I might actually buy 1 or 2 more for when these actually do die out. Hope this helps. Ah... and I never leave Amazon reviews. haha.

These headphones have performed better than expected for this price point. They sound much better than any other ear buds (wireless or wireless) that I have currently. They sync quickly and easily. The range us excellent. The only issue I have is that if you are using them to work out, the band that connects the left and right bud tends to stick to moist skin in the back of the neck. However, I discovered a fix. If I allow the band to hang down in the front this ceases to be a problem. Overall, this was a great purchase. I got a great Bluetooth headset that functions admirably yet I won't be too distraught if they are lost or stolen as they are reasonably priced and I'll just buy another one.

For the price these headphones are amazing. The sound quality is alright but for 30 dollars you can't really complain, also they are completely noise cancelling. The ear hooks are a pretty flimsy but surprisingly they stay on your ears even during intense workouts. I've done plyometric workouts and weightlifting and they never fell off. The battery life is also pretty great, you can have the volume up loud and they last 8 hours which is two more hours than most other brands. These also come with a carrying case, 3 different ear tips, two charging cords, and a car charger. This is a great deal and I definitely recommend them to anyone who wants a good pair of Bluetooth headphones and not spend hundreds of dollars.

They are sweat resistant and stay on my ears through any activity. Come with 3 different sizes of inner ear pieces. The part around your ear is like silicone and super flexible, which I think makes them fit better than being a hard plastic. Connect perfectly every time, long range, never an issue there. I wouldn't call these noise cancelling, but the sound quality is seriously amazing! They can also get super loud, too. I would highly recommend these to anyone with an active lifestyle. Whether you're deadlifting, running, hiking, or anything in between, I would highly recommend!

I couldn't tell from the from the product description or the review comments if the earbuds pause button would pause my Kindle Fire HD and/or my Amazon Fire Stick but I went ahead and ordered them anyway. THEY WORK on both!! I'm very, very happy! I may, in the future, want to upgrade to a set of Bluetooth earbuds that can pair with more than 2 devices but these are a great introduction into the technology. I'm 65 years old and moderately technologically competent - but I'm no expert! - and the instruction book was really easy to follow. All the extra earbud sizes that came in the box were such a wonderful addition. I am a small woman with very small ear canals so nothing ever fits. While not perfect, the smallest ones are sufficient for my needs. (I'm not overly physically active-mostly hiking.) I didn't understand what the tiny little squares were - another inclusion in the box - and there was no information to explain them. I did some research and found a couple of You Tube videos that helped me understand that they were cable management devices to help create a custom fit. I'd have liked that information to be in the instruction booklet. I don't really get the benefit but I'll do some playing around and see if I have an unknown "need" for cable management on an earbud strap! Who knows? I may end up realizing I had a problem that needed that solution! Bottom line, I am delighted with this purchase!

I needed headphones that would provide me a bit of freedom moving around outside without a cord tethered to my iPhone. The cost for the BHS-730 was low, so I my expectations for sound quality were not very high. However, I have to say that after listening to these for about an hour or so, I was more than please with the sound quality. I listen to mainly hard rock/metal, but also podcasts or radio shows. For music, the bass was good, not muddied, highs were clear and not overly crisp. Fit overall was very good, and the headphones are supplied with a host of different size eartips, and even some extra parts, all in a nice zipper case. I have only used them for about an hour, so I am not sure on the overall battery life per charge. Overall I am quite happy with my purchase. Less than $40 bucks gives you a nice sounding, untethered pair of earbuds that sound great! That's hard to beat!

Nice for the office so I can get up and walk to the printer without removing earbuds.I've worn them about 15 hours before I got a low battery notification. Love that I can control calls and skip through music from the on-cord control. Pretty good for running. Nice not to have to worry about a cord. They aren't heavy and the sound is good. I did have to start wearing my hair in a braid or bun because my ponytail would brush against the cord and cause noise and tug them loose. The left ear definitely fits snug and secure, good seal, the right ear isn't as tight. I debated trying some of the other (tons) of buds that came with it to get a better fit - but decided to leave it because I can hear cars coming behind me better on the right this way - I really can't hear any outside noise on the left. Also, the on-cord volume control is on the right. I really like being able to tuck the cord over my ear on the left, but it wasn't as good on the right because the control got in the way. I just left it hang down on the right side since it's looser anyway. It's so nice to skip songs on my playlist from the headphones instead of trying to look at my phone while I run. Update: After a few months I just keep these in my office to use at my desk. I got a $10 pair of bluetooth headphones from Target that at much more lightweight and comfortable to use for running. Still worth the money, but not the best option out there for fitness.

these are the first wireless headphones i've ever used. they were easy to set up and easy to use. my friend said the microphone works better on these then on the headphone/mic that came with my iphone. i really appreciate the company sending multiple ear fitting options.makes it easy to find an option that works and is comfortable. they even come with a pair that fit snug like earplugs. i also like the fact that they join magnetically. i can wear them around my neck without losing them. Definitely worth the money if you're looking for a way to listen to music or talk on the phone without wires. i really dig the color choices too!

Great product. Don't think because the price is low, the quality isn't high. These earbuds have great sound and come with a lot of different earpiece options. The range is better than other cordless Bluetooth headphones I have owned, and they automatically reconnect smoothly if you do leave the range of your device. The foam noise blocking ear pieces keep out noisy kids and airplane engine noise alike. They are also water resistant so you can jam out in the hot tub or jog in the rain without worrying about water damage. If you need to remove them, the magnets hold them securely around your neck until you're ready to listen again. What more could you want? The battery life isn't infinite, but how long can you expect a tiny battery that fits in your ear to last? All in all, these headphones are probably the best deal in Bluetooth headphones out there. They also come from a small company that wants you to be satisfied and stands behind their product.

I wish there was an option for zero stars......the product worked great for 20 minutes, then it shut off. When I restarted it I had to re-pair it with my phone.....it worked again for about ten minutes, shutting off again. Restart it , re-pair it......and there was a mix of audio and static....and I couldn't turn it off.........RETURNED !I bought this because of the very good ratings it was getting, and for the price, had it worked it would have been great........but alas....you get what you pay for.

I bought these earbuds for working out and running. I have now used them for both. The problem I have with earbuds is that they fall out of my ears and irritate me when I have to readjust mid-run or workout. These stay in my ears quite well. I like the magnetic clip to keep them around my neck instead of searching for them. They do stick out of my ears slightly, which I thought would bother me, but I have gotten used to that aspect. In the mirror though, I do notice it. They are easier to operate than other sets I have had. The volume works well. Pairing was easy.

Finally. These earbuds were not a success out the door, but the amazing customer support won me over. After the owner asked me if I liked the earbuds, and I responded that they were not holding a charge, he promptly sent out new ones. I'm sure the defect is a rarity, and unfortunately, so is this kind of customer service. Most companies would not take the time or the effort to pursue their customers to the degree that this company does. They want the consumer to be happy with their product, and for that reason alone, these earbuds are priceless. As for the earbuds themselves, the sound is clear, with good treble, (although I'd love a bit more bass), but the earbuds come with enough earbud pieces to satisfy a team of people. The case is compact, and the earbuds fit nicely and are easily wearable for a duration of time. Between the customer service and the quality earbuds, and the very reasonable price, you can't go wrong..

I am so absolutely thrilled. I finally found a Bluetooth that works. I have tried so many Bluetooth's in the 10 years I've had my car and finally gave up hope in finding one that would work both ways in my loud Mustang GT. Either the caller couldn't hear me or I couldn't hear them. My son is the one person who consistently could never hear me and I was always having to turn the volume up as high as it would go to hear him, but ended up with more distortion than words. He was the first person I called on my drive home today and the first time I tried the Phaiser Earbuds and he could hear me perfectly and best yet is that I could hear him like he was in the next room and without turning up the volume once. It was awesome. I'll keep you updated as the more people and places that I reach out to to continue the review, but as of right now I'm giving it a high thumbs up! Thank you, thank you, thank you. It is more appreciated than you'll ever know Oh and it's being used on my Samsung Galaxy Note 7. Love the Phaiser Earbuds.

I am about a week into using these bluetooth headphones, and I bring them with me everywhere. The battery life has been great and pairing them has been incredibly easy. The magnetic feature has been a huge plus as I can stick them together and tuck them inside my shirt when I don't need them. The are made if aluminum I believe, so they feel solid. They are heavier than a typical wired ear bud, but that is understandable considering the need for a battery in them. This is not the highest quality audio, but considering the price point, I am beyond satisfied. Working with the seller was great. Excellent communication with regards to shipping and delivery.

Martin, The owner and product specialist from 7Desk / Phaiser sent me an email to let me know that my new BHS-730 Bluetooth Earbuds were on the way and if I had any questions To get in touch with him directly by replying to the email he sent. Well the Earbuds arrived fast and were very easy to set up to work with my iPhone. Great sound it was nice that Martin attached a users manual and a QuickStart Guide to the email. Thank You

I was going to spend a lot more money on an alternate brand and a friend recommended these. I'm beyond impressed with both the function and audio quality. I'm an audiophile and musician, but I know when to balance sound vs. convenience. I bought these for work and have ended up using them for much more. I use the comply tips (thank goodness they come with Comply's) and they don't budge. Bass is a little high but not too bad -- I've owned much, much worse. Good enough soundstage and they connect quickly. The battery will say 'high' until it's about to die, then it says 'low' and you have about 5 minutes max. One thing where the Phaiser's are truly remarkable is in how they fit the ear. I've used countless other earbuds in the past and none ever fitted the way this have. There's none of the usual vacuum or discomfort, even after prolonged times (2 to 4 hours). And the outside sound-blocking is great.

This is the dinkiest little Bluetooth ear bud imaginable. It comes inside a polythene bag within a box measuring just 60mm x 35mm x 20mm - barely bigger than a matchbox. Also inside the box is an ‘elbowed’ USB charging dock, similar in size to a memory stick, and an instruction booklet. Eager to try it out, I plugged it into my laptop, to charge, as soon as it arrived it. The neat little charging dock can be connected to the laptop straight, or bent at a right angle, and it can also be plugged into a USB car charger, which is very useful. The bud charged up surprisingly quickly, but I forgot to time it. I then paired it with my iPhone, and took the dog out for a walk, with my phone safe in my deep pocket. I rarely listen to music on my phone (other than SongPop) so the fact that this is a single bud doesn’t matter to me. I primarily wanted it for when I’m dog walking, and for when I’m driving - as the sound between my phone and SatNav is poor above the road noise, engine, open windows, and outside noises. I don’t need stereo sound when using it in these situations…. and if I ever do want stereo sound I have other headphones for that. What I like about this glossy little single bud is that I when I’m wearing it when walking or driving I do not feel isolated/cut off from the world, as I can and still hear people talking to me, and other sounds - like traffic or a cyclist approaching me from behind. I therefore feel this single bud is safer for use outside the home, and I do not feel vulnerable or disorientated. For charging, the bud attaches to the USB via mighty powerful magnets within. You can feel the pull (and hear a metallic click) as they grab each other. Charging is indicated by a blue light. The sound of this tiny gadget is good, and it’s easy to use in all respects. The only downside is that it is extremely small, rounded, and glossy, so it’s quite difficult to hold between the fingers, and it’s very easy to misplace, or to lose it altogether. Also, it doesn’t stay in my ear as well as the ‘rubberised’ silicone buds and, once I’ve finished using it, it’s difficult to know how to carry it if not in my ear. It could so easily slip out of a pocket (and has done so). So saying, I don’t think it will disappoint. IF MY REVIEW HAS BEEN HELPFUL TO YOU, PLEASE CLICK ON THE 'YES' BUTTON BELOW. THANK YOU.

For so long I have been fed up with battling against tangled earphones in order to listen to my music- until I found this little gem. I absolutely LOVE it. Without a doubt the smallest bluetooth headphone I've ever owned/seen. Comes nicely packaged in a small box. A nice shiny black when taken out, smooth and well refined. Lightweight and feels good in the hand. Comes with a few spare buds for various ear sizes. A circle shape, the whole outside of the headphone is a button which when pushed gives a reassuring click. Pressing and holding this button down for a few seconds turns the earpiece on. Holding it further down puts it in pairing mode. Pairing is straightforward and no passcodes were required.A blue/red light shine from behind the button which is noticeable, but not annoying. A tiny button on the underside of the earpiece serves as the volume button. Pressing it rotates the volume up. When the maximum volume is reached, you hear a beep. A further press of the button brings the volume back down to the lowest volume. In the box you also get another earpiece connected to a cable ending in a micro USB cable in case you want to use it in stereo. When connected to the USB port on the main earpiece (which also serves as the charging port), it works flawlessly. Battery life seems spectacular with me using it regularly for three full days without it losing output yet. I have yet to see how long it will last before it needs recharging. Making and taking calls through this is fantastic with no one aware I was using a hands-free set. Voice quality is fantastic. Listening to music is equally fantastic. Surprisingly good bass and excellent treble. Overall, a fantastic bluetooth headset which is unbelievably small yet powerful.

So, if you want something small without getting those completely hidden away in-ear things you see in spy movies (which would probably cost an arm and a leg), this might just be the one to get.

I am extremely happy with my purchase of this product--it's much better than competing screen protectors I've bought, especially those for sale at the Apple Store.  A few tips for people who intend to buy and use this product:#1.  The instructions recommend that you apply the screen protector in the bathroom after letting hot water steam up for a few minutes.  This is a VERY GOOD IDEA.  Definitely helped keep the dust away.#2.  If you're going to be applying more than one screen protector at once, be aware that the cloth included with the product does a very good job of wiping away and catching dust . . . however, that means that on subsequent applications, the cloth can leave dust particles on the phone that it had previously swept off on prior applications.  I had to really shake out the cloth in between applications and make sure that it didn't leave any trail of dust.#3.  Be careful when using the rubber bands.  They can snap pretty easily if you're rough.Overall, though, I do not plan to buy any other brand of screen protector going forward.  The product and process of this one is hands down the best.

So far I am happy with this screen protector, but I did just get it yesterday. I am 100% satisfied with this product. The headlight is very sturdy and attractive. The mount stays firmly in place on my handlebar even during very rough trail riding. The light is much brighter than I expected and very visible even at dusk. The tail light also stays firmly mounted to my seat-post and is very bright. The fact that the headlight can detach from the mount is very handy in case you need to use it as a handheld flashlight, remove it to charge it, or remove it to hose down your bike (in case you don't want to get it wet, although I have ridden with it in the rain with no problem). The fact that the headlight is USB rechargeable means you don't have to worry about replacing batteries or toting around an external battery as I have seen with more powerful headlights. I honestly would say anything brighter than this is overkill for most applications. If you need a solid headlight and tail light, this is the way to go. The quality and versatility of these lights is outstanding especially when considering the price.

He has Down syndrome and I wanted to make sure he will have enough light to see the road ahead while driving at night and also for cars and other bikers to see him on the bike. This light is good for children, normal adults and people like my brother whom may react a little slower in certain situations. I think this light is a good investment for your safety.

Product is great. Easy to mount to bike. Brightness of the lights is more than satisfactory. Certainly not a reason to not buy it though. It's a fantastic product for the price point. I highly recommend.

Best pair of wireless earbuds have owned in quite a while, and I've gone through 4. Firstly, the earbuds came a week earlier than Amazon had predicted, so kudos to the company! I wanted to purchase wireless earbuds to work out in and replace my wired earbuds with. Yet, the last time I purchased Bluetooth earbuds, they broke within a week of use. I by no means abuse my electronics either--other than the normal wear and tear associated with wearing them. The earbuds themselves provide the standard functions and accessories I’ve come to expect from my audio devices. An LED light indicates if the earbuds are charging and turns off if it is fully charged. If you have the earbuds in your ear, it will also tell you the battery level by voice. Newer Bluetooth capable devices (laptops, phones, etc.) can show you the battery level on the screen as well. Unfortunately, my phone does not and I have the Note 4. The case the earbuds came in contained a diverse plethora of replacement tips for the earbuds so I won’t have to worry about losing some. There are of course volume control and pause/play buttons on the cord for easy access. An equalizer mode is available for those who want to further tune their listening experience. Quality and sound-wise, I would say these babies could challenge my BOSE headphones and definitely my Bluetooth BEATS. I am no master when it comes to critiquing music sound quality, but these earbuds provided a content experience for me. Overall, I would heartily recommend these earbuds to those looking for a mid-tier costing pair of earbuds. For the price you’re paying, you will most likely get your money’s worth.

I don't normally leave reviews so... Martin and his team at 7Desk / Phaiser are all over customer service. I had a concerned about the earbuds on this model and they reached out to me to solve it. Price? Cannot beat it. This headset is solid. Sound is good. Music & audio books are crystal clear. Phone calls are really clear. And everyone tells me they can hear me just fine. My only issues is with the earbuds. And it's just a personal preference. I like the in-the-ear type. These are the in-the-ear canal type which are the most common. In that respect, they work great. Not my optimal choice but better then all the others I bought and tried. I'll repeat - good solid produce, great price, amazing customer service.

I did my homework looking for high quality reasonably priced wireless headphones for the gym and other outdoor activities. I read a ton of reviews and quickly found poor reviews on the most popular brands that were also priced ridiculously to the point of being insulting to the consumer. When I read the reviews for Phaiser, I was INTERESTED! The reviews were spot on. I use them with my iPhone and they're great. Sound quality exceeded my expectations! It's great! The case is perfect and of good quality. I was also impressed with the extra ear pieces provided to find justb the right size. And lastly, this company has already impressed my with their customer care and service! I will be a faithful customer and refer my friends! HIGHLY RECOMMEND!

Love this thing! I can get approximately 40 ft away before the connection starts cracking. Fully charged, it lasts me about 5 hours straight. It comes with multiple ear bud sizes and types. I'm a 120 lb. girl and use the smallest ones with the inner ear hook and it fits fine. I've had to buy smaller buds before (for reference). I haven't worked out with it yet but I don't anticipate any issues with them falling out at all. Setup was a breeze. Sound is great. I've used it to listen to music, do modules on my computer, and talk on the phone. I didn't have any issues hearing the other person nor did they hearing me.

I wanted to give these ample time before writing a review so that I can give a fair review of the product. For starters, the battery on these headphones last pretty long. Having to travel for work every week, I can typically go a few days without needing any kind of charge. The best part is the sound. Since purchasing these headphones, I have flown on a 738, 757, A330, a tiny regional jet and a two prop plane and every time I could hear my movies clearly and loudly. The noise cancelling works very well and I couldn't be happier. The only slight drawback is that these headphones are about twice as big as other manufacturers, but they work amazing. Highly recommend!!!

There are so many attachments/accessories to this; although the instructions do not include what every attachment is for, I really like the product. I have small ears and finding a comfortable and functional bluetooth set has been difficult. I have tried every headset out there and thought I would give this a shot. I'm happy to say I'd give this a 5 star rating for the following reasons: - 5 star comfort - 5 star functionality - 5 star ease of set up and use - 5 star for use for intense workouts - trail running, cycling, any kind of cardio. these stay put - 5 star value Overall great product.

I recently purchased a pair of these headphones with the intention of using them at the gym. I'm extremely hard on headphones because the cord gets tangled with the weights. These stay securely in place and out of the way while still having a great sound quality. I had a small issue with a manufacturing defect and contacted the seller through Amazon. They took care of the problem and I have never been happier. I am currently getting somewhere between 5-5.5 hrs on a charge. Great product and will do business with this seller again.

This is a great buy! Dollar for dollar is well worth it. The unit itself is simple in design, functional, and easy to operate. The control unit is easy to manipulate functions. Sound is very good, loud an clear. The ear buds fit comfortably. My only issue and it is no longer an issue is the size of the earbuds. Once you realize no one is looking at you, all it good. Especially important and appreciated is owner contact. He has shown concern for customer satisfaction and is seemingly available for any issues if any come up. That service level is unique in todays commercial world. Buy two of them, you can always use a second one.

The sound is amazing and it really does shut out the white noise. I will be buying another set for my brother since he's constantly breaking his headphones that come with the phone.

Clean Look. I would have liked the brushed aluminum look but that's not an option with the 24 oz Byron. Matte Black I think looks better than the only other color option they have for the 24 oz Byron. It's threading is better than the 20 oz Contigo mug I bought about a year ago. Not only does it screw on faster, easier, and feels more secure, but I've also tested it for leakage and absolutely none. Does a GREAT job at keeping my coffee as hot as it was when I poured it in there. So much so that I actually let it sit with the lid off for a little bit because if I don't it will still feel just as pipping hot 2 hours later. I also like how the Matte Black isn't paint. The lid is BPA free and is easy to clean. I love it.

I am writing the review based on my first time using the mug - and I will update if it does not hold true to a 5 star rating. To start, the mug has a sleek design, I brewed the largest cup on my Keurig, added creamer, and still had room with the 16 ounce version of the mug. The insulation on this cup is so great that it felt cool to the touch on the outside. I went through my morning routine and didn't drink my coffee until about an hour and a half later when I arrived at work and it was still piping hot! No other mug I've owned has kept my coffee so hot. I tipped the mug upside down while sealed and nothing leaked. So far I am a huge fan and I'm considering buying a second mug.

I bought this mug at a different store, not Amazon. It's the best travel mug I've ever used. I put this in my handbag or in a side pocket of my backpack and it has never leaked. It's always roughly upright in my bag but I don't think it would leak even if it wasn't. It's great for my subway commute where I'm standing and need to hold on with one hand, and like to use the other hand to read the news on my phone. I've used travel mugs that don't completely seal, but those have to be held so that they don't spill, which makes it impossible to also read the news. It also keeps liquid piping hot during my 40 minute commute, which includes a lot of time outside in the cold Boston winter weather. Liquids stay warm for several hours. This mug has paid for itself many times over as I'm now making coffee at home instead of buying it near work for $3/day. Love it!

Wonderful product. Just have to be careful not to put the liquid in too hot if planning on drinking out of the cup right away. Follow the directions and there is really no problem getting the lid on as indicated in some reviews. I've had other travel cups where I didn't get the lid on correctly because of being in too much of a hurry to get going. This is no different -- do it right and no problem. Try to rush -- problem. Great cup for sipping your beverage. Who plans to take a big gulp of a hot beverage anyhow. That was the complaint of some reviews but again, no problem unless you try to take a big gulp of a steaming beverage.

I've been using this cup for some time and I absolutely love it. It doesn't leak, and it does a pretty decent job of insulating my hot coffee.
